# Changelog

All notable changes to WiFi Refresh Utility are documented here.

## [1.0.0] - 2026-07-06

### Added
- A portable AutoHotkey-based tray launcher with a dedicated refresh action and a DNS-only action
- A separate [scripts/flush-dns.ps1](scripts/flush-dns.ps1) workflow for clearing the DNS cache without reconnecting Wi-Fi
- A notification toggle that can be changed from the tray menu or persisted in [scripts/notification-enabled.ini](scripts/notification-enabled.ini)
- Automatic telemetry logging to [scripts/Telemetry](scripts/Telemetry) for actions and failures
- A prebuilt [togglewifi.exe](togglewifi.exe) launcher alongside the script source

### Changed
- The PowerShell backend now uses BurntToast for notifications and attempts to install it automatically on first run
- The launcher now exposes direct menu actions for viewing logs and opening the telemetry folder
- The repository documentation was updated to reflect the current tray workflow and file layout

### Fixed
- Notification issues are now recorded in the error log instead of failing silently
- The scripts create the telemetry folder automatically before writing logs

## [0.3.0] - 2026-06-30

### Changed
- Replaced the legacy C# toast helper with the BurntToast module
- Removed the previous dependency on a compiled helper executable for notifications

### Fixed
- Resolved the broken toast-notification flow that previously failed to surface banners reliably

## [0.2.5] - 2026-06-29

### Added
- Initial AutoHotkey tray launcher
- PowerShell backend for DNS and ARP cleanup plus Wi-Fi reconnect
- Notification toggle via INI configuration

### Known issues
- Toast notifications could fail silently due to the earlier helper approach
- The workflow required a compiled helper for notifications on first run

---